Word Origin and History for sociology Expand. n. the science of social phenomena, 1843, from French sociologie, a hybrid coined 1830 by French philosopher Isidore Auguste Comte (1798-1857), from Latin socius associate (see social (adj.)) + Greek-derived suffix -logie (see -logy).
</BODY>
